{
  "info": {
    "_postman_id": "1c8cf438-bd48-45df-95d0-949dd2931beb",
    "name": "ANF Migrate",
    "description": "This collection provides a step-by-step workflow for migrating volumes to **Azure NetApp Files (ANF)** using external replication. It covers the full migration lifecycle, from initial setup through to cutover, using the Azure NetApp Files REST API.\n\n---\n\n## Folders\n\n### Setup\nEstablishes the replication relationship between the source (external ONTAP cluster) and the ANF target volume:\n\n1. **Step 0. Authorization** — Obtains an OAuth2 bearer token required to authenticate all subsequent API calls.\n2. **Step 1. Create Target Volume** — Provisions the destination ANF volume configured for external replication.\n3. **Step 2. Check Volume Creation Progress** — Polls the async operation to confirm the target volume is ready.\n4. **Step 3. Issue Cluster Peer Request** — Initiates cluster peering between the external ONTAP cluster and ANF.\n5. **Step 4. Get Cluster Peering Command & Passphrase** — Retrieves the peering command and passphrase needed to complete the cluster peer on the source side.\n6. **Step 5. Authorize External Replication** — Authorizes the replication relationship, allowing data transfer to begin.\n7. **Step 6. Get Vserver Peering Command** — Retrieves the SVM/vserver peering command to finalize the peer relationship on the source cluster.\n\n### Pre-Cutover and Cutover\nManages the final replication sync and the cutover to the ANF volume:\n\n1. **Change Replication Schedule** — Adjusts the replication schedule in preparation for cutover (e.g., increasing frequency).\n2. **Issue Re-Sync Request** — Triggers a manual replication transfer to minimize data lag before cutover.\n3. **Issue Break Relationship Request** — Breaks the replication relationship, making the ANF volume writable for cutover.\n4. **Get Async ID – Break** — Polls the async operation to confirm the break has completed.\n5. **Issue Finalize External Replication** — Finalizes the external replication setup post-cutover.\n6. **Get Async ID – Finalize** — Polls the async operation to confirm finalization is complete.\n\n---\n\n## Prerequisites\n- An active Azure subscription with ANF configured (account, capacity pool, and resource group).\n- Valid Azure AD credentials to obtain an OAuth2 token.\n- Environment variables set for: `authcloudurl`, `apicloudurl`, `tenant`, `subscriptionId`, `resourceGroupName`, `accountName`, `poolName`, `api-version`, and `ma.volumeName`.",
    "schema": "https://schema.getpostman.com/json/collection/v2.1.0/collection.json",
    "_exporter_id": "949385",
    "_collection_link": "https://go.postman.co/collection/949385-1c8cf438-bd48-45df-95d0-949dd2931beb?source=collection_link"
  },
