      "description": "Establishes the replication relationship between the source (external ONTAP cluster) and the ANF target volume. Run these steps in order before initiating data replication.\n\n**Steps**\n\n1. **Step 0. Authorization** — Obtains an OAuth2 bearer token required to authenticate all subsequent API calls. The token is stored as a global variable and is valid for one hour.\n2. **Step 1. Create Target Volume** — Creates (or updates) the destination volume in the specified ANF capacity pool, configured to receive external replication data.\n3. **Step 2. Check Volume Creation Progress** — Polls the async operation URL to confirm the target volume has been successfully provisioned before proceeding.\n4. **Step 3. Issue Cluster Peer Request** — Initiates a cluster peering request between the ANF volume and the external ONTAP source cluster.\n5. **Step 4. Get Cluster Peering Command & Passphrase** — Retrieves the peering command and passphrase that must be run on the source ONTAP cluster to complete the cluster peer relationship.\n6. **Step 5. Authorize External Replication** — Authorizes the external replication relationship on the ANF target volume, enabling data transfer from the source.\n7. **Step 6. Get vServer Peering Command** — Retrieves the vServer peering command to be executed on the source cluster, finalizing the SVM-level peer relationship required for SnapMirror replication.",
